Text.Value: I can promise you fewer secrets?
I promise you - I'll sate myself on our foes alone from now on.
No need to deny it. The bat's out of the bag, so to speak.

EditorData.NodeContext: Good natured but not letting the player get away with it

Text.Value: Say nothing. Stare into Gale's eyes, unblinking.
A vamp, huh? Interesting. Keep your teeth to yourself, Astarion, and we won't have any issues.
...How did you figure that out?
Anyway, you'd burn your tongue off if you went for this neck.
I've had my suspicions about you for some time now. And there you go, confirming them with truly audacious gusto.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character saw Astarion use his 'bite' ability on someone else (probably in combat, but not necessarily) and confronts him about being a vampire.

Text.Value: You almost said that without smiling.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry, knows Astarion's a bit of a trickster

Text.Value: For his sake, he best not develop an appetite for githyanki.
I know what it is to have an uncontrollable hunger within you. You can hardly be blamed for your desperation in trying to satisfy it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere, but not giving too much away (referring to the orb, which he may or may not have told the player about)

Text.Value: Nothing wrong with a bit of caution, I suppose. Better to sound out friends and enemies alike before revealing that kind of secret.
As you're not willing to engage in a frank conversation on the matter, I think we'll leave it there.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not impressed, knows you've lied to him

Text.Value: I'm sure you could have found your way around that with a bit of imagination.
Aha! I knew it. I knew you'd try something like that eventually. Though I wish you'd done it with a bit less enthusiasm.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character was bitten by Astarion in gameplay.
EditorData.NodeContext: At first triumphant - Gale'sbeen proved right about something (which he loves to be, of course). Then feeling the smart of Astarion's attempted bite.
EditorData.logicalname: WAS BITTEN BY AST IN GAMEPLAY

Text.Value: Still, I can hardly blame a vampire for being true to its nature. You are a vampire, are you not?
Thank you  for trusting me.
I'd just better not wake in the night to find fangs at my throat.
I see. You're a dishonest vampire, and that's far worse.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not impressed, knows you've lied to him

Text.Value: Very well - but I'm keeping an eye on you. And no wisecracks about having us for supper.
Couldn't be further off the mark.
As I said, I'm willing to move past the whole exsanguination issue, so long as you can promise to keep that hunger of yours in check.
*Sigh.* I suppose that will do for now. But none that pose the threat of imminent death or destruction, for me, or yourself, or anyone else for that matter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Like admonisihing a puppy, knows Astarion will just do what he wants

Text.Value: Well then - let's hope you've strength to spare.

EditorData.NodeContext: unsure - player didn't exactly promise not to feed on him again

Text.Value: I thought I'd awaken feeling, well, drained. But I seem to be quite as well as ever.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Avatar Astarion tried to bite this companion during the night, but you woke up and discovered he was a vampire. You talked it through and resolved things peacefully in CAMP_AstarionHunger_IVB_SCO_Avatar_Choice.lsj

Text.Value: I'm quite open-minded. It's one of my finer qualities, and there's some stiff competition in that department.
A choice both efficient and pragmatic. Most unlike you.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a smile - poking fun at Astarion's flair for the flamboyant

Text.Value: I'll take that as a no, shall I? *Sigh*. It was worth a try.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not overly bothered, didn't think this would work

Text.Value: Still, there was no real harm done. So long as you can keep that craving of yours in check, I'm happy that our paths remain aligned.
Yeah. And I'm way too hot to touch.
Do not undersell yourself, you may not have the grand lair nor loyal swarm but a vampire spawn is still part of the vampire family. Technically.
Given our group's nature, I don't see much harm. We're each monsters in the making, after all.

EditorData.logicalname: Check more than one party member

Text.Value: But should I wake with so much as a drop of blood on my neck, I will end him.
So, we move forwards. And when the occasion arises, we show our enemies exactly how sharp those teeth of yours can be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrapping up the topic, determination wabout what comes next

Text.Value: There was nothing friendly about what you just did to me. But I'll humour you - we'll call that a momentary lapse in good sense, shall we?
Most people don't react as well as you.
I'll resist with all my strength.
The ability to walk in broad daylight, for example, with not a burn in sight. I suppose we have your parasite to thank for that.
I can see the truth in that. But you and I aren't 'most people'.
Fine - as long as he keeps his fangs off our necks.
At first I wasn't sure. Some of your behaviour doesn't exactly match what my traveller's tomes describe of one of your... disposition.
But as for the rest - well, there can be only one conclusion. You're a vampire.
A vampire? Well that explains the pallor.
And how are you this morning, my blood-thirsty friend?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Avatar Astarion tried to bite A DIFFERENT companion during the night, but they woke up and discovered he was a vampire. They talked it through and resolved things peacefully in CAMP_AstarionHunger_IVB_SCO_Avatar_Choice.lsj
EditorData.NodeContext: Eyebrow raised - still not entirely convinced Astarion is to be trusted

Text.Value: I'm telling you, I'm not a vampire.
With that said, I'm more than happy to continue onwards. But no more hiding things from me. Agreed?
I'm happy to draw a line under the matter and move forward. But from here on, no more hiding things from me. Agreed?

EditorData.NodeContext: Stern, not very impressed about it but willing to move on

Text.Value: But why weren't you honest with me?
I don't care if you eat blood or boiled eggs for breakfast, but if we're to survive this parasitic adventure of ours, we have to trust each other.
There's open-minded, and then there's 'happy to sleep next to a vampire spawn.' I didn't think you'd like it much.
Now, unless you've any other deep, dark secrets to own up to, shall we continue on?
Vamps don't scare me. As long as they keep their teeth to themselves.
Admittedly, that's not saying much given our ongoing predicament. Nonetheless, I'm glad I woke up when I did.
Hunting with vampires? Never thought I'd see the day.
I had no choice. My old master put a curse on me. Forbade me ever revealing my true nature.
I am. But I'm a friendly one - I promise.
The real conundrum here is why weren't you honest with me?
No more secrets, on my honour.
No sense judging someone for who they are. Except devils, obviously.
If you'd had your way our number would be one fewer by now. We're fortunate you were caught red-fanged.
You're a vampire.
Oh, it was quite easy, really. I took note of certain abilities you possessed, certain aspects of your behaviour depending on our environment. And those teeth of yours. Quite the pair of canines.
I can tell you what I don't like. Unwittingly sleeping next to someone with a taste for blood and a tendency to lie about it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, but willing to move past it

Text.Value: How tragic. Well, lucky for you your master couldn't predict the observational cunning of our troupe's resident Waterdhavian wizard. Your silence spoke volumes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleased with himself for figuring this out

Text.Value: Technically I'm a vampire spawn.
A vampire among us? So be it.
I think it's about time you and I had a little chat. An honest one.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Companion confronts Avatar Astarion, telling him they know he's a vampire. Triggers if you make it to Act 2 without him telling you himself or revealing it via camp night bite scene/using bite attack in front of you.

Synopsis: Gale's default dialog that triggers whenever you speak to Gale in the game world. Covers a variety of topics that mostly react to Gale-related events that took place.
